properties.name: Waste Lands
properties.description:
No land is without purpose, even if that purpose is solely its own. Of course, most measures of a land's purpose are somewhat arbitrary human inventions, but we are rather selfish creatures, prone to classifying things according to our own whims and desires. When the land's purposes do not align with our own, we do not always react with grace or subtlety. This week: the wastes.
